At victor-gadbois, in cooperation with a group of volunteers, body care is provided with the help of nutrition.
This is what palliative care looks like, which comes into being if nothing else can be done.
To make death more comfortable.
In Quebec, one palliative care bed per 11,700 inhabitants.
That's very little if we realize we're all going to die someday.
Here life continues in optimal conditions, explains Dr. Christiane Martel, one of the doctors in the home.
Whether it is a level of physical, emotional or spiritual comfort.
When a person dies, for example, a taste of brandy or pepsi can be provided.
