But the pity is completely unnecessary, because people with disabilities are no sufferers of all the abandoned beings we have to regret.
These are people who can live a full life and develop, provided, of course, that they have the necessary means to do so.
I say that when people with disabilities succeed, it's not just a shift for them, it's a shift for society as a whole.
