Despite opposition from some states, the EU has already softened standards on fruit and vegetables, pointing out that existing directives lead to food waste.
Last year's EU regulation, under which inflatable balloons sold must be compulsory, must also be a candidate for winning the poll, as well as a mandatory warning that children under the age of 8 must not inflate them unattended by adults.
