I ran away.
Yes, I ran away because I was subjected to systematic bullying and intimidation.
Not because of my rather bizarre name or the fact that I came from private school.
I was persecuted for one reason, and in this cradle of supposed enlightenment it was both bigoted and barbaric: my father, the late Woodrow Wyatt, was a senior adviser to Margaret Thatcher, and I was a Conservative Party supporter.
